      "text": [
        "هِ اَلْجَنَابَةُ فَيَعْرَقُ فِيهِ فَقَالَ «إِنَّ اَلثَّوْبَ لاَ يُجْنِبُ اَلرَّجُلَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.151 - Abdullah ibn Bakir asked Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) about a man who wears a garment with janabah (ritual impurity from sexual activity) and sweats in it.\nImam (as) said: 'The garment does not make the man ritually impure.'."
        ]
      }
